last_episode_to_air.name: Not a Ghost Yet

name: Not Dead Yet
overview: Nell Serrano is a broke and newly single self-described disaster. She works to restart the life and career she left behind some 10 years ago. When writing obituaries is the only job she can find, Nell starts getting life advice from an unlikely (and dead) source.
tagline: She's taking ghost writing to a whole new level.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Nell attempts to restart her life in a new place with a new job and a new roommate. She begins writing obituaries at the local paper and starts getting life advice from an unlikely source.

episodes.name: Not a Tiger Yet
episodes.overview: As Nell tries to settle into her new job, she gets increasingly annoyed by her latest ghost. Meanwhile, Edward works on a project that sparks Nell’s journalistic curiosity.

episodes.name: Not Out of High School Yet
episodes.overview: Nell is asked to write an obituary for a popular influencer with whom she has history. Elsewhere, Sam helps Dennis overcome an old fear.

episodes.name: Not Dating Yet
episodes.overview: Nell’s friends rally to set her up on some dates, but Nell isn’t sure she’s ready to move on. Edward has better luck finding a match.

episodes.name: Not Moving On Yet
episodes.overview: After Nell falls for the wrong guy, she realizes her last relationship may be holding her back. Meanwhile, Edward helps Cricket decide that what’s missing from the bar is a bit of her past.

episodes.name: Not Ready to Share Yet
episodes.overview: Lexi puts Sam in charge of the newspaper’s food and wine festival, making Nell jealous of their friendship. At the event, Edward helps Cricket with her booth and Dennis lets off some marital steam.

episodes.name: Not Out of the Game Yet
episodes.overview: Nell’s father comes to visit. Meanwhile, Lexi conducts the employees’ yearly performance review at the SoCal Independent.

episodes.name: Not Friends Yet
episodes.overview: Nell finally meets Edward’s girlfriend. Meanwhile at the wine bar, Cricket hosts trivia night.

episodes.name: Not Scattered Yet
episodes.overview: With Nell’s help, Cricket decides to finally spread Monty’s ashes. Sam and Lexi support Dennis as he chooses an egg donor.

episodes.name: Not Well Yet
episodes.overview: After a fun night out with Sam and Dennis, Nell winds up sick in bed and wanting to be left alone. Meanwhile, Lexi convinces Sam and Dennis to join her for lunch, which spirals into a much longer commitment.

episodes.name: Not Feeling It Yet
episodes.overview: After months of processing her relationship with Phillip, Nell tells Sam she's ready to move on. Sam tries to recapture her spark with her husband. Lexi helps Dennis search for the perfect egg donor.

episodes.name: Not a Fairytale Yet
episodes.overview: Nell agrees to see Phillip, hoping for closure. Sam and Lexi have a joint birthday party for their daughters.

episodes.name: Not Just Yet
episodes.overview: Nell holds a dinner party at her house and Dennis has to make a potentially life-altering decision.

episodes.name: Not Owning It Yet
episodes.overview: Lexi's father and owner of the SoCal Independent, Duncan Rhodes, comes into the office and forms a bond with Nell, much to his daughter's dismay.

episodes.name: Not a Valentine Yet
episodes.overview: After receiving some truth from Cricket on Valentine's Day, Nell realizes she may be using ghosts as an excuse to not open herself up to love.

episodes.name: Not in the Cards Yet
episodes.overview: Lexi, Duncan, Sam and Dennis attend an award ceremony for several SoCal Independent editing nominations. Meanwhile, Nell steps in to babysit Sam's daughter, who doesn't seem interested in hanging out with her "fun Aunt Nell."

episodes.name: Not Polite Yet
episodes.overview: Lexi combines the first two floors of the newsroom, leaving Nell to share a cubicle with T.J., a popular sportswriter who’s friends with everyone… except her.

episodes.name: Not Solved Yet
episodes.overview: When Nell's latest ghost is convinced that there was foul play involved in his death, Nell is happy to try to investigate until Lexi inserts herself into the case.

episodes.name: Not Going Home Yet
episodes.overview: Nell grows frustrated with Lexi and Edward's relationship; the newsroom staff pulls an all-nighter.

episodes.name: Not in the Game Yet
episodes.overview: TJ asks Nell to play on the newspaper softball team. Lexi and Edward spend a weird version of quality time together, while Duncan runs into an old rival.

episodes.name: Not You Yet
episodes.overview: Nell, Lexi and Cricket take Sam out on a "divorce day" to celebrate her singlehood, while Nell makes plans for her future.

episodes.name: Not the End Yet
episodes.overview: Nell finds out that Duncan is selling the SoCal Independent, so she takes matters into her own hands to save her job when Lexi seems unwilling to help.

episodes.name: Not a Ghost Yet
episodes.overview: Nell navigates an unexpected incident that leaves the sale of the newspaper on hold.
